ate General)\n*{{SGP}}\n** [[Singapore]] (Embassy)\n*{{KOR}}\n** [[Seoul]] ([[Embassy of the United States, Seoul|Embassy]])\n** [[Busan]] (Consulate)\n*{{LKA}}\n** [[Colombo]] (Embassy)\n*{{SYR}}\n** [[Damascus]] (Interests Section in Czech Embassy){{NoteTag|Effective February 6, 2012, the embassy suspended operations and closed for normal consular services. Since March 1, 2013, a U.S. Interests Section operates via the Government of the Czech Republic through its embassy in Damascus. Only emergency services for U.S. citizens are available. Neither U.S. passports nor visas to the United States can be issued in Damascus.}}\n*{{ROC-TWN}}{{NoteTag|The United States [[Foreign relations of Taiwan|does not formally recognize]] the [[Taiwan|Republic of China on Taiwan]]. Unofficial relations are conducted through the [[American Institute in Taiwan|AIT]], a ''de facto'' embassy.}}\n** [[Taipei]] ([[American Institute in Taiwan]]\u2014Taipei Office)\n** [[Kaohsiung]] ([[American Institute in Taiwan Kaohsiung Branch Office|American Institute in Taiwan\u2014Kaohsiung Branch Office]])\n*{{TJK}}\n** [[Dushanbe]] (Embassy)\n*{{THA}}\n** [[Bangkok]] ([[Embassy of the United States, Bangkok|Embassy]])\n** [[Chiang Mai]] (Consulate General)\n*{{TUR}}\n** [[Ankara]] (Embassy)\n** [[Istanbul]] ([[Consulate General of the United States, Istanbul|Consulate General]])\n** [[Adana]] (Consulate)\n** [[Izmir]] (Consular Agency)\n*{{TKM}}\n** [[Ashgabat]] (Embassy)\n*{{UAE}}\n** [[Abu Dhabi]] ([[Embassy of the United States, Abu Dhabi|Embassy]])\n** [[Dubai]] ([[Consulate General of the United States, Dubai|Consulate General]])\n*{{UZB}}\n** [[Tashkent]] (Embassy)\n*{{VNM}}\n** [[Hanoi]] (Embassy)\n** [[Ho Chi Minh City]] ([[Consulate General of the United States, Ho Chi Minh City|Consulate General]])\n{{div col end}}\n\n<gallery widths=\"200px\" heights=\"160px\">\nFile:American Embassy in Amman.jpg|U.S. Embassy in [[Amman]]\nFile:U.S. Embassy in Baghdad, Iraq.png|[[Embassy of the United S